@module codegen
@lang aria
@aid_version 0.2
@layer 2
@purpose IR lowering, LLVM IR generation, ARM64 emission, and Mach-O linking
@depends [lexer, parser, resolver, checker, diagnostic]
@workflow Source code enters via generate_from_source or generate_from_sources, flows through lex -> parse -> resolve -> check -> lower -> LLVM IR -> clang -> native binary. The LLVM backend is the primary path; ARM64 emitter and Mach-O builder are the dormant native-emission path.

---

@type IrOp
@kind sum
@variants
  OpConst -- Integer constant
  OpConstStr -- String constant reference
  OpAdd -- Integer addition
  OpSub -- Integer subtraction
  OpMul -- Integer multiplication
  OpDiv -- Integer division
  OpMod -- Integer modulo
  OpNeg -- Integer negation
  OpEq -- Equality comparison
  OpNeq -- Inequality comparison
  OpLt -- Less than
  OpGt -- Greater than
  OpLte -- Less than or equal
  OpGte -- Greater than or equal
  OpAnd -- Logical AND
  OpOr -- Logical OR
  OpNot -- Logical NOT
  OpBitAnd -- Bitwise AND
  OpBitOr -- Bitwise OR
  OpBitXor -- Bitwise XOR
  OpShl -- Shift left
  OpShr -- Shift right
  OpCall -- Direct function call
  OpCallIndirect -- Indirect function call (closures)
  OpFnRef -- Function reference (for closures)
  OpRet -- Return with value
  OpRetVoid -- Return void
  OpArg -- Function argument reference
  OpLocal -- Local variable reference
  OpStore -- Store to local
  OpLoad -- Load from local
  OpFieldGet -- Struct field read
  OpFieldSet -- Struct field write
  OpAlloc -- Heap allocation
  OpArrayNew -- Create new array
  OpArrayGet -- Array element read
  OpArraySet -- Array element write
  OpArrayLen -- Array length
  OpArrayAppend -- Array append
  OpStrLen -- String length
  OpStrConcat -- String concatenation
  OpStrEq -- String equality
  OpStrCharAt -- Character at index
  OpStrSubstring -- Substring extraction
  OpStrContains -- String contains check
  OpStrStartsWith -- String starts-with check
  OpStrEndsWith -- String ends-with check
  OpStrIndexOf -- String index-of
  OpStrTrim -- String trim
  OpStrReplace -- String replace
  OpStrToLower -- String to lowercase
  OpStrToUpper -- String to uppercase
  OpStrSplit -- String split
  OpIntToStr -- Integer to string conversion
  OpStrToInt -- String to integer conversion
  OpMapNew -- Create new map
  OpMapSet -- Map set key-value
  OpMapGet -- Map get by key
  OpMapContains -- Map contains key check
  OpMapLen -- Map length
  OpMapKeys -- Map keys
  OpSetNew -- Create new set
  OpSetAdd -- Set add element
  OpSetContains -- Set contains check
  OpSetLen -- Set length
  OpSetValues -- Set values
  OpSetRemove -- Set remove element
  OpJump -- Unconditional jump
  OpBranchTrue -- Branch if true
  OpBranchFalse -- Branch if false
  OpLabel -- Label definition
  OpTraitObject -- Create trait object
  OpVtableCall -- Virtual dispatch call
  OpArraySlice -- Array slice operation
  OpNop -- No operation
@source_file src/codegen/ir.aria
@source_line 11
@purpose Flat enum of all IR opcodes. Each instruction in the linear IR carries one of these. The IR is intentionally untyped at the opcode level -- type information lives in IrInst.type_id and IrFunc.temp_types. String operations (OpStr*) and collection operations (OpMap*, OpSet*, OpArray*) lower to runtime function calls in the LLVM backend.
@invariants Every IrFunc instruction list must end with OpRet or OpRetVoid; the emitter/LLVM gen inserts a fallback if missing.
@notes OpNop is used as the sentinel instruction in arrays (index 0 is always a sentinel per Aria array convention). OpCallIndirect supports closure dispatch by calling through a function pointer.

---

@type IrInst
@kind struct
@fields
  op: IrOp -- Operation code
  dest: i64 -- Destination temp register
  arg1: i64 -- First argument (temp or immediate)
  arg2: i64 -- Second argument
  s1: str -- String argument (function names, string constants)
  type_id: i64 -- Type ID for typed operations
@source_file src/codegen/ir.aria
@source_line 168
@purpose Flat instruction format for the linear IR. All fields are present on every instruction but their meaning varies by opcode: for OpCall, s1 is the target function name and arg1/arg2 carry arguments; for OpConst, arg1 is the integer value; for OpConstStr, arg1 is the string constant index and arg2 is the string length.
@invariants dest must be a valid temp index within the enclosing IrFunc; arg1/arg2 interpretation is opcode-dependent.
@notes The fixed-width struct avoids sum type overhead. Unused fields default to 0/"".

---

@type IrFunc
@kind struct
@fields
  name: str -- Function name
  param_count: i64 -- Number of parameters
  insts: [IrInst] -- Instruction list
  return_type: i64 -- Return type ID
  local_count: i64 -- Number of local variables
  temp_types: [i64] -- Type IDs for temporaries
@source_file src/codegen/ir.aria
@source_line 185
@purpose Represents one function in the IR module. param_count is the number of register-level parameters (strings count as 2: ptr + len). temp_types tracks per-temp type info used by the LLVM generator for GC root analysis.
@invariants insts[0] is always a sentinel OpNop instruction. temp_types[0] is always 0 (sentinel). Valid type IDs: 0=unknown, 1=i64, 12=str, 100+=struct type.
@notes func_inst_count returns insts.len()-1 to account for the sentinel.

---

@type IrModule
@kind struct
@fields
  funcs: [IrFunc] -- All functions
  string_constants: [str] -- String constant pool
  entry_func: str -- Entry function name
  test_count: i64 -- Number of test functions
  test_names: [str] -- Test function names
  extern_names: [str] -- External function names
  extern_param_counts: [i64] -- External function param counts
  extern_ret_types: [str] -- External function return types
  extern_libs: [str] -- External library names
@source_file src/codegen/ir.aria
@source_line 219
@purpose Top-level compilation unit. Collects all lowered functions, deduplicated string constants, FFI declarations, and test metadata. Passed to the LLVM generator or ARM64 emitter.
@invariants All arrays use index-0 sentinels. funcs[0] is a sentinel function. string_constants[0] is "". entry_func must name a function present in funcs (typically "_main").
@notes extern_* parallel arrays track FFI declarations. test_names stores human-readable test labels for the test runner.

---

@type Lowerer
@kind struct
@fields
  tokens: [Token] -- Token stream
  pos: i64 -- Current position
  store: TypeStore -- Type store from checker
  registry: TypeRegistry -- Type registry from checker
  treg: TraitRegistry -- Trait registry from checker
  pool: NodePool -- AST node pool
  table: SymbolTable -- Symbol table
  file: str -- Source file path
  module: IrModule -- Module being built
  current_func: IrFunc -- Current function being lowered
  temp_counter: i64 -- Next temp register ID
  label_counter: i64 -- Next label ID
  env_names: [str] -- Variable name environment
  env_slots: [i64] -- Variable slot mapping
  loop_start: i64 -- Current loop start label
  loop_end: i64 -- Current loop end label
  const_names: [str] -- Constant integer names (pre-scanned)
  const_vals: [i64] -- Constant integer values
  const_str_names: [str] -- Constant string names (pre-scanned)
  const_str_vals: [str] -- Constant string values
  temp_types: [i64] -- Per-temp type tracking (0=unknown, 1=i64, 12=str, 100+=struct)
  fn_error_type: i64 -- Error type for current fallible function (0=not fallible)
  defer_count: i64 -- Number of active deferred expressions
  defer_start_0..7: i64 -- Token start positions for up to 8 deferred expressions
  defer_end_0..7: i64 -- Token end positions for up to 8 deferred expressions
@source_file src/codegen/lower.aria
@source_line 19
@purpose Mutable state threaded through the multi-pass lowering process. Mirrors the checker's token-walking pattern. env_names/env_slots form a stack-based variable environment mapping names to temp register slots.
@invariants pos must be within bounds of tokens array. current_func is only valid during function body lowering. loop_start/loop_end are -1 when not inside a loop.
@notes The Lowerer struct is rebuilt on every mutation (Aria has immutable bindings, so functional update is required). The 11K-line lower.aria file does three passes: (1) _scan_consts collects compile-time constants, (2) _lower_bodies lowers all fn/entry/test blocks, (3) _lower_derives generates trait derive implementations, followed by _lower_mono_pass for generic monomorphization.
@antipatterns Do not access current_func outside of a begin/finish function pair. Defer slots are fixed at 8 max -- exceeding the limit now emits an error message (previously silently dropped). Field access on unresolved struct types falls back to _field_index_any (first-match across all structs); type-aware resolution via _struct_name_for_type is preferred when the object's type is tracked.

---

@type LT
@kind struct
@fields
  l: Lowerer -- Updated lowerer state
  temp: i64 -- Result temp register
@source_file src/codegen/lower.aria
@source_line 67
@purpose Return type for lowering expressions. Pairs the updated lowerer state with the temp register holding the expression's result. Equivalent to the checker's CE pattern.
@notes Every _lower_expr* function returns an LT. The caller must use the returned l (not the original) to maintain state consistency.

---

@type LlvmGen
@kind struct
@fields
  parts: [str] -- LLVM IR text parts
  label_counter: i64 -- Next label ID
  last_was_term: bool -- Whether last instruction was a terminator
@source_file src/codegen/llvm.aria
@source_line 176
@purpose Accumulates LLVM IR text for a single function using an array of string parts. Parts are joined via divide-and-conquer _join() to avoid O(n^2) string concatenation.
@invariants last_was_term tracks whether the previous instruction was a terminator (br, ret, unreachable) to avoid emitting unreachable code after terminators, which LLVM rejects.
@notes The streaming file writer (_generate_llvm_ir_to_file_target) generates each function's IR independently, joins it, writes to disk, and discards -- avoiding holding the full 22MB+ IR in memory.

---

@type LT_label
@kind struct
@fields
  g: LlvmGen -- Updated generator state
  id: i64 -- Generated label ID
@source_file src/codegen/llvm.aria
@source_line 198
@purpose Return type for fresh label allocation. Pairs updated LlvmGen state with the new label's numeric ID.

---

@type Emitter
@kind struct
@fields
  code: [i64] -- Machine code words
  label_offsets: [i64] -- Label to code offset mapping
  pending_branches: [PendingBranch] -- Unresolved branches
  pending_calls: [PendingCall] -- Unresolved call targets
  pending_strings: [PendingString] -- Unresolved string references
  frame_size: i64 -- Stack frame size
  temp_count: i64 -- Number of temp registers
@source_file src/codegen/emit.aria
@source_line 11
@purpose ARM64 machine code emitter state. Uses a spill-everything register allocation strategy: every IR temp gets a stack slot, loaded before use and stored after definition. Branch/call/string fixups are deferred and patched after all instructions are emitted.
@invariants code[0] is sentinel (0). All pending_* arrays use index-0 sentinels. frame_size is always 16-byte aligned.
@notes This is the dormant native-emission path. The primary compilation path uses LLVM IR + clang.

---

@type PendingBranch
@kind struct
@fields
  code_index: i64 -- Position in code array
  label_id: i64 -- Target label
  is_cond: bool -- Whether conditional
  cond: i64 -- Condition code
  reg: i64 -- Register for CBZ/CBNZ
  is_cbz: bool -- CBZ vs CBNZ
@source_file src/codegen/emit.aria
@source_line 21
@purpose Records an unresolved branch instruction that needs its offset patched once the target label's position is known.

---

@type PendingCall
@kind struct
@fields
  code_index: i64 -- Position in code array
  target_name: str -- Target function name
@source_file src/codegen/emit.aria
@source_line 33
@purpose Records an unresolved BL (branch-with-link) instruction. Patched by the linker/codegen once all function offsets are known.

---

@type PendingString
@kind struct
@fields
  code_index: i64 -- Position in code array
  string_id: i64 -- String constant ID
  dest_temp: i64 -- Destination temp
  str_len: i64 -- String length
@source_file src/codegen/emit.aria
@source_line 41
@purpose Records an unresolved string constant load (ADR instruction placeholder). Patched once the cstring data section's position relative to the code is known.

---

@type RuntimeFunc
@kind struct
@fields
  name: str -- Runtime function name
  code: [i64] -- ARM64 machine code
@source_file src/codegen/runtime.aria
@source_line 14
@purpose Pre-assembled ARM64 machine code for runtime support functions. Used by the dormant native Mach-O backend. The LLVM backend instead declares these as external symbols resolved by the C runtime library.
@invariants code[0] is sentinel (0). name must match the symbol expected by the emitter (prefixed with _aria_).

---

@fn generate_from_source
@sig (source: str, file: str, output_path: str, runtime_path: str) -> DiagnosticBag
@calls [tokenize, build_decl_index, resolve, check, lower, generate_llvm_ir]
@source_file src/codegen/codegen.aria
@source_line 19
@purpose Full single-file compilation pipeline: lex -> parse -> resolve -> typecheck -> lower -> LLVM IR -> clang. Returns diagnostics; an empty bag with no errors indicates success.
@workflow Entry point for single-file compilation. Each stage bails early on errors.
@effects Reads source file, writes .ll file, invokes clang via _ariaExec to produce native binary.
@errors Returns DiagnosticBag with errors from any failed stage (lex, parse, resolve, check, or clang invocation). Clang failure produces error code E9000.
@pre source must be valid UTF-8. runtime_path must point to the compiled C runtime library.
@post On success, output_path contains a native executable and output_path.ll contains the LLVM IR.

---

@fn generate_from_module
@sig (m: IrModule, output_path: str, runtime_path: str) -> DiagnosticBag
@source_file src/codegen/codegen.aria
@source_line 49
@purpose Generates LLVM IR from an already-lowered IrModule, writes it to a .ll file using streaming (to avoid 22MB+ memory spike), then invokes clang to compile and link against the runtime.
@effects Writes output_path.ll via generate_llvm_ir_to_file. Executes clang via _ariaExec. Creates native binary at output_path.
@errors E9000 if clang compilation fails (returns non-zero exit code).
@notes Uses clang flags: -O1 for optimization, -Wno-override-module to suppress target triple warnings.

---

@fn generate_from_sources
@sig (files: [str], output_path: str, runtime_path: str) -> DiagnosticBag
@calls [generate_from_source]
@source_file src/codegen/codegen.aria
@source_line 121
@purpose Multi-file compilation pipeline. Lexes each file independently, merges token streams (stripping duplicate mod/use headers), then runs the full pipeline on the merged tokens.
@workflow Used by the CLI for multi-file builds. Token merging preserves file ordering and strips mod/use declarations from non-first files to produce a single unified token stream.
@effects Reads all source files via _ariaReadFile. Writes .ll file and native binary.
@pre files must have at least 2 elements (index 0 is sentinel, actual files start at index 1).
@antipatterns Files must all declare the same module name. The merge strips mod/use from subsequent files but does not validate module name consistency.

---

@fn check_sources
@sig (files: [str]) -> DiagnosticBag
@calls [tokenize, build_decl_index, resolve, check]
@source_file src/codegen/codegen.aria
@source_line 165
@purpose Check-only mode: runs lex, parse, resolve, and typecheck without lowering or code generation. Used by the CLI `check` command.
@effects Reads source files via _ariaReadFile.
@post Returns diagnostics from the typecheck stage (or earlier if a stage fails).

---

@fn generate_tests_from_sources
@sig (files: [str], output_path: str, runtime_path: str) -> DiagnosticBag
@source_file src/codegen/codegen.aria
@source_line 194
@purpose Test compilation pipeline: same as generate_from_sources but uses lower_for_tests instead of lower. This compiles test blocks and generates a _main test runner that calls each test function, prints PASS/FAIL, and exits.
@effects Reads files, writes .ll and binary.
@notes Entry blocks are skipped during test lowering to avoid _main conflicts with the generated test runner.

