@fn lower
@sig (tokens: [Token], index: DeclIndex, pool: NodePool, store: TypeStore, reg: TypeRegistry, treg: TraitRegistry, table: SymbolTable, file: str) -> IrModule
@source_file src/codegen/lower.aria
@source_line 11247
@purpose Main lowering entry point. Runs four passes: (1) _scan_consts pre-scans compile-time constants, (2) _lower_bodies lowers all fn/entry/test bodies to IR, (3) _lower_derives generates trait derive implementations (Eq, Clone, Debug, Display, Default, Ord, Hash), (4) _lower_mono_pass generates monomorphized copies of generic functions.
@workflow Called after check() succeeds. Produces an IrModule ready for LLVM IR generation.
@pre All inputs must come from a successful check pass. tokens/pool/store/registry/treg/table must be consistent.
@post Returns an IrModule with entry_func set, all functions lowered, and string constants populated.
@notes Match lowering uses a peek-ahead to detect data sum types; named patterns (binding @ Variant) are handled by skipping past the binding and @ token to find the actual variant name. [src: lower.aria:9876-9895] Optional chaining (?.) resolves the inner struct type from the Optional's type_id for correct field index lookup. [src: lower.aria:4497-4504]

---

@fn lower_for_tests
@sig (tokens: [Token], index: DeclIndex, pool: NodePool, store: TypeStore, reg: TypeRegistry, treg: TraitRegistry, table: SymbolTable, file: str) -> IrModule
@source_file src/codegen/lower.aria
@source_line 11258
@purpose Test-mode lowering. Same as lower() but skips entry blocks (to avoid _main conflicts) and appends a generated test runner _main that calls each _test_N function, prints "PASS: <name>" for each, prints "all tests passed", and exits 0.
@post entry_func is set to "_main" (the generated test runner). Each test block becomes _test_0, _test_1, etc.
@notes The test runner calls _before/_after fixture functions (if they exist in the module) around each test invocation. Fixtures are lowered from `before { }` / `after { }` blocks in the source.

---

@fn generate_llvm_ir
@sig (m: IrModule) -> str
@source_file src/codegen/llvm.aria
@source_line 265
@purpose Generates complete LLVM IR text for the module as a single string. Delegates to _generate_llvm_ir_target with target "native" (arm64-apple-macosx14.0.0).
@notes For large programs this can produce 22MB+ strings. Prefer generate_llvm_ir_to_file for production use.
@antipatterns Holding the full IR string in memory can cause OOM for large programs. Use generate_llvm_ir_to_file instead.

---

@fn generate_llvm_ir_to_file
@sig (m: IrModule, path: str) -> unit
@source_file src/codegen/llvm.aria
@source_line 272
@purpose Streaming LLVM IR writer. Generates each function's IR independently, joins it via divide-and-conquer _join(), writes to disk via _ariaWriteFile, and discards. Avoids holding the entire IR in memory.
@effects Writes LLVM IR text to the file at path.
@notes Uses chunked string joining: groups of 64 parts joined first, then chunks joined. This gives O(L * N/64) instead of O(L * N) string concatenation.
@workflow Called by generate_from_module as the primary code generation path.

