@type Emitter
@note_group ARM64 Emitter (dormant native path)

@fn new_emitter
@sig () -> Emitter
@source_file src/codegen/emit.aria
@source_line 51
@purpose Creates an empty Emitter with all sentinel arrays in place.

---

@fn emit_function
@sig (f: IrFunc) -> Emitter
@calls [new_emitter]
@source_file src/codegen/emit.aria
@source_line 133
@purpose Emits ARM64 machine code for a single IR function. Calculates frame size (16-byte aligned), emits prologue (STP x29/x30, set frame pointer, allocate stack), stores incoming arguments (x0-x7) to stack slots, emits each IR instruction via _emit_ir_inst, appends epilogue if needed, and resolves branch fixups. [src: emit.aria:133]
@pre f must have valid instruction list with sentinel at index 0.
@post Returns Emitter with complete machine code, resolved branches, and pending calls/strings for linker fixup.
@notes Uses spill-everything register allocation: every temp is in a stack slot. Loads into x0/x1 before operations, stores result back. Simple but correct. ARM64 ABI: first 8 args in x0-x7.

