# --- Mach-O Builder ---

@fn build_macho
@sig (code_words: [i64], cstring_data: [i64], entry_offset: i64) -> [i64]
@source_file src/codegen/macho.aria
@source_line 542
@purpose Builds a complete Mach-O 64-bit ARM64 executable as a byte array. Includes all required load commands (13 total), __PAGEZERO, __TEXT segment with __text section, __LINKEDIT with chained fixups and exports trie, and an embedded ad-hoc SHA-256 code signature. No external tools needed. [src: macho.aria:542]
@pre code_words[0] is sentinel. cstring_data[0] is sentinel. entry_offset is in instruction words (multiplied by 4 for byte offset).
@post Returns byte array (with sentinel at index 0) ready to be written to disk as an executable.
@effects Pure computation -- no I/O.
@invariants MH flags must be MH_PIE | MH_TWOLEVEL | MH_DYLDLINK | MH_NOUNDEFS (0x200085). __TEXT segment is page-aligned. LINKEDIT has no gaps. Code signature covers all pages up to code_limit.
@notes Load commands: __PAGEZERO, __TEXT, __LINKEDIT, LC_DYLD_CHAINED_FIXUPS, LC_DYLD_EXPORTS_TRIE, LC_SYMTAB (empty), LC_DYSYMTAB, LC_LOAD_DYLINKER (/usr/lib/dyld), LC_UUID (deterministic), LC_BUILD_VERSION (macOS 26.0), LC_MAIN, LC_LOAD_DYLIB (libSystem.B.dylib), LC_CODE_SIGNATURE. Targets macOS 26 ARM64 specifically.
@antipatterns Do not omit any of the 13 load commands -- the kernel silently SIGKILLs binaries missing required ones. LC_UUID must be present or dyld crashes.

---

