# --- Runtime Function Builders ---
# These build pre-assembled ARM64 machine code for the dormant native Mach-O backend.
# They use macOS ARM64 syscall convention: x16 = syscall number, x0-x5 = args, SVC 0x80.
# Syscall numbers: exit=1, write=4, read=3, open=5, close=6, chmod=15, mmap=197, fstat64=339.

@fn build_exit_runtime
@sig () -> RuntimeFunc
@source_file src/codegen/runtime.aria
@source_line 25
@purpose Builds _aria_exit(code): terminates process via exit syscall (x16=1). Leaf function, never returns.
@notes 2 instructions: MOVZ x16, #1; SVC 0x80. No prologue/epilogue needed since it never returns.

---

@fn build_write_runtime
@sig () -> RuntimeFunc
@source_file src/codegen/runtime.aria
@source_line 35
@purpose Builds _aria_write(fd, ptr, len): write syscall (x16=4). Leaf function -- no prologue needed. Returns bytes written in x0.
@notes 3 instructions: MOVZ x16, #4; SVC 0x80; RET.

---

@fn build_println_str_runtime
@sig () -> RuntimeFunc
@source_file src/codegen/runtime.aria
@source_line 48
@purpose Builds _aria_println_str(ptr, len): writes string to stdout followed by a newline. Non-leaf (uses stack for locals). Performs two write syscalls: one for the string, one for the newline character stored on the stack.
@notes 20 instructions. Allocates 32 bytes of stack. Writes to fd=1 (stdout).

---

@fn build_alloc_runtime
@sig () -> RuntimeFunc
@source_file src/codegen/runtime.aria
@source_line 95
@purpose Builds _aria_alloc(size): heap allocation via mmap syscall (x16=197). Each call independently mmaps a page-aligned region with PROT_READ|PROT_WRITE, MAP_PRIVATE|MAP_ANON.
@notes Simplified per-call mmap strategy (no bump allocator). Size is aligned to 16 bytes before mmap. Returns pointer in x0.
@antipatterns Every allocation gets its own mmap -- wasteful for small allocations. Acceptable for the native backend which is dormant.

---

@fn build_memcpy_runtime
@sig () -> RuntimeFunc
@source_file src/codegen/runtime.aria
@source_line 130
@purpose Builds _aria_memcpy(dst, src, len): byte-by-byte copy loop using LDRB/STRB post-index. Leaf function.
@notes 6 instructions. Handles zero-length with CBZ skip. Not optimized (byte-at-a-time), suitable for small copies.

---

@fn build_read_file_runtime
@sig () -> RuntimeFunc
@source_file src/codegen/runtime.aria
@source_line 148
@purpose Builds _aria_read_file(path_ptr, path_len) -> (ptr, len): reads entire file into memory. Copies path to stack and null-terminates it, then uses open (syscall 5), fstat64 (syscall 339) to get file size, mmap (syscall 197) to allocate buffer, read (syscall 3), and close (syscall 6). Returns fat pointer (ptr in x0, len in x1).
@notes ~50 instructions. Allocates 256 bytes of stack for locals + stat buffer. File size extracted from stat_buf offset 96. Includes inline byte-copy for path (cannot call _aria_memcpy since runtime functions cannot reference each other).

---

@fn build_write_binary_file_runtime
@sig () -> RuntimeFunc
@source_file src/codegen/runtime.aria
@source_line 249
@purpose Builds _aria_write_binary_file(path_ptr, path_len, data_ptr, data_len): writes a byte array to a file. data_ptr is an Aria [i64] array where each element holds one byte value. Converts [i64] to byte buffer via mmap + loop, then writes. Uses open (O_WRONLY|O_CREAT|O_TRUNC, 0755), write, close, and chmod (syscall 15).
@notes ~60 instructions. Skips sentinel element at array index 0. Sets file permissions to 0755 (executable).

---

@fn build_int_to_str_runtime
@sig () -> RuntimeFunc
@source_file src/codegen/runtime.aria
@source_line 355
@purpose Builds _aria_int_to_str(val) -> (ptr, len): converts i64 to decimal string. Handles negative numbers (prepends '-'). Extracts digits via repeated division by 10 into stack buffer (reverse order), then copies to mmap-allocated buffer. Returns fat pointer.
@notes ~50 instructions. Handles zero as special case. Stack buffer at [sp+24..sp+47] holds up to 24 digits. Digit extraction: SDIV by 10, MUL back, subtract for remainder.

---

@fn build_args_runtime
@sig () -> RuntimeFunc
@source_file src/codegen/runtime.aria
@source_line 450
@purpose Builds _aria_args() -> array_ptr: returns the command-line args array. Simply returns X19, which is callee-saved and set by the entry trampoline via _aria_args_init.
@notes 2 instructions: MOV x0, x19; RET. Leaf function.

---

@fn build_args_init_runtime
@sig () -> RuntimeFunc
@source_file src/codegen/runtime.aria
@source_line 463
@purpose Builds _aria_args_init(argc, argv) -> array_ptr: converts C argc/argv into an Aria [str] array. Allocates array header (24 bytes: length, capacity, data_ptr) + data ((argc+1) * 16 bytes for sentinel + elements). Each string element is a fat pointer (ptr, len). Computes string length via inline strlen loop (scan for null byte).
@notes ~58 instructions. Array layout: header at base, data at base+24. data[0] is sentinel (0,0). data[1..argc] point directly to argv strings (no copy). String pointers are borrowed from the process argv (valid for program lifetime).

